# Coding standards

- TypeScript strict mode.
- SOLID: keep route handlers thin; business logic lives in services.
- Keep services dependency-injected and unit-testable.
- Prefer pure functions for compilation logic.
- Prefer small, explicit types instead of any.

Errors:
- Throw errors in services; translate to HTTP responses in routes.
- Never leak secrets in error messages.

Comments:
- Only add comments for complex logic or security reasoning.
